    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-09-03T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-09-03T04:00:00-05:00" n="301"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <head>301. Telegram 3448 From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Ethiopia</gloss> to
                    the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d301fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, DEF 15 ETH–US.
                        Secret; Limdis. Repeated to Asmara, CINCSTIKE, and Kagnew Station.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d301fn2">The Chargi reported that the
                        Ethiopian Foreign Minister welcomed the proposed personnel reductions at
                        Kagnew Station.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Addis Ababa</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1970-09-03T09:00:00+00:00">September 3, 1970, 0900Z</date>
                </dateline>
                <pb facs="d301-01" n="1" xml:id="d301-01"/>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Personnel Reduction Kagnew Station</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Ref:</head>
                    <item>(A) State 138074; (B) Asmara 0487</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. Charge this morning made points outlined reftel (A) to FonMin Ketema Yifru. As
                    result earlier approach to Ketema (Addis 33761) latter had apparently had chance
                    to consider response. Said his position had not changed and that he welcomed
                    U.S. move, which should be helpful to him and colleagues in IEG who come under
                    pressure from those criticizing presence U.S. “base” in Ethiopia. From context
                    conversation this reaction applies also to probable further reductions noted
                    reftel, of which Charge informed him.</p>
                <p>2. CT has been briefed in terms outlined reftel and will be informed above
                    developments at meeting next week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Yost</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
